00074 /* This function specifies the macro registers that are assumed to be killed */
00075 /* by jsr's, so returning a 1 means killed. */
00076 
00077 /* output and return params are fragile (can't be moved over function call)  */
00078 
00079 int
00080 M_starcore_fragile_macro (int macro_value)
00081 {
00082 
00083   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00084     {
00085       switch (macro_value)
00086         {
00087         case L_MAC_P0:
00088         case L_MAC_P1:
00089         case L_MAC_P2:
00090         case L_MAC_P3:
00091         case L_MAC_P4:
00092         case L_MAC_P5:
00093         case L_MAC_P6:
00094         case L_MAC_P7:
00095 
00096           /* Integer output parameters */
00097         case L_MAC_P8:
00098         case L_MAC_P9:
00099         case L_MAC_P10:
00100         case L_MAC_P11:
00101         case L_MAC_P12:
00102         case L_MAC_P13:
00103         case L_MAC_P14:
00104         case L_MAC_P15:
00105 
00106           /* Integer return parameters */
00107         case L_MAC_P16:
00108         case L_MAC_P17:
00109         case L_MAC_P18:
00110         case L_MAC_P19:
00111 
00112           /* FP input/output parameters */
00113         case L_MAC_P20:
00114         case L_MAC_P21:
00115         case L_MAC_P22:
00116         case L_MAC_P23:
00117         case L_MAC_P24:
00118         case L_MAC_P25:
00119         case L_MAC_P26:
00120         case L_MAC_P27:
00121 
00122           /* FP return parameters */
00123         case L_MAC_P28:
00124         case L_MAC_P29:
00125         case L_MAC_P30:
00126         case L_MAC_P31:
00127 
00128         case STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT:
00129         case STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT_INV:
00130         case STARCORE_MAC_SR:
00131 
00132         case L_MAC_OP:
00133           return (1);
00134 
00135         default:
00136           return (0);
00137         }
00138     }
00139   else
00140     {
00141       M_assert (0, "M_starcore_fragile_macro: illegal machine model");
00142       return (0);
00143     }
00144 }

00198 /****************************************************************************
00199  *
00200  * routine: M_starcore_extra_pred_define_opcode()
00201  * purpose: Determine if the proc_opc opcode generates a predicate.
00202  *          Only machine specific predicate generating opcodes above and
00203  *          beyond the normal pred defines, clears, and stores need to be
00204  *          listed.
00205  * input:
00206  * output:
00207  * returns: 1 if the opcode generates a predicate.  0 otherwise
00208  * modified: Bob McGowan, 9/11/96 created
00209  *           Mark Tozer   5/30/97 added cmp4_ne_and for pred_clear
00210  * note:
00211  *       Add new opcodes to one of the 
00212  *           M_starcore_extra_pred_define_typeX functions, too (mbt)
00213  *-------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
00214 
00215 int
00216 M_starcore_extra_pred_define_opcode (int proc_opc)
00217 {
00218 
00219   switch (proc_opc)
00220     {
00221     case STARCOREop_CMPEQ:
00222     case STARCOREop_CMPGT:
00223     case STARCOREop_CMPHI:
00224     case STARCOREop_DECEQ:
00225     case STARCOREop_DECGE:
00226     case STARCOREop_TSTEQ:
00227     case STARCOREop_TSTGE:
00228     case STARCOREop_TSTGT:
00229     case STARCOREop_CMPEQA:
00230     case STARCOREop_CMPGTA:
00231     case STARCOREop_CMPHIA:
00232     case STARCOREop_DECEQA:
00233     case STARCOREop_DECGEA:
00234     case STARCOREop_TSTEQA_L:
00235     case STARCOREop_TSTEQA_W:
00236     case STARCOREop_TSTGEA:
00237     case STARCOREop_TSTGTA:
00238     case STARCOREop_BMTSTC:
00239     case STARCOREop_BMTSTC_W_2:
00240     case STARCOREop_BMTSTC_W_3:
00241     case STARCOREop_BMTSTS:
00242     case STARCOREop_BMTSTS_W_2:
00243     case STARCOREop_BMTSTS_W_3:
00244       return (1);
00245     default:
00246       return (0);
00247     }
00248 }

00311 
00312 int
00313 M_starcore_subroutine_call (int opc)
00314 {
00315 
00316   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00317     {
00318       switch (opc)
00319         {
00320         case Lop_JSR:
00321         case Lop_JSR_FS:
00322           /* Library calls */
00323         case Lop_DIV:
00324         case Lop_DIV_U:
00325         case Lop_REM:
00326         case Lop_REM_U:
00327         case Lop_ABS_F:
00328         case Lop_ABS_F2:
00329         case Lop_ADD_F:
00330         case Lop_ADD_F2:
00331         case Lop_DIV_F:
00332         case Lop_DIV_F2:
00333         case Lop_MUL_F:
00334         case Lop_MUL_F2:
00335         case Lop_RCMP_F:
00336         case Lop_SUB_F:
00337         case Lop_SUB_F2:
00338         case Lop_F_I:
00339         case Lop_F2_I:
00340         case Lop_I_F:
00341         case Lop_I_F2:
00342         case Lop_BR_F:
00343           return 1;
00344         default:
00345           return 0;
00346         }
00347     }
00348   else
00349     {
00350       M_assert (0, "M_starcore_subroutine_call:  Illegal model specified!");
00351       return (0);
00352     }
00353 }

00358 /* return 1 for macros that should be included in dataflow analysis */
00359 
00360 int
00361 M_starcore_dataflow_macro (int id)
00362 {
00363 
00364   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00365     {
00366       switch (id)
00367         {
00368         case STARCORE_MAC_TEMPLATE:
00369         case STARCORE_MAC_LABEL:
00370           return FALSE;
00371         default:
00372           return TRUE;
00373         }
00374     }
00375   else
00376     {
00377       M_assert (0, "M_starcore_dataflow_macro: illegal machine model");
00378       return (0);
00379     }
00380 }

00382 /*
00383  * Declare code generator specific macro registers to the front end parser.
00384  */
00385 
00386 void
00387 M_define_macros_starcore (STRING_Symbol_Table * sym_tbl)
00388 {
00389 
00390   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00391     {
00392       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "sp", STARCORE_MAC_SP);
00393       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "sr", STARCORE_MAC_SR);
00394       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "tmp", STARCORE_MAC_TEMP);
00395       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "Template", STARCORE_MAC_TEMPLATE);
00396       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "Label", STARCORE_MAC_LABEL);
00397 
00398       /* 1 if leaf function, 0 if non-leaf */
00399       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "$leaf", STARCORE_MAC_LEAF);
00400       /* LV space for int spill around sync */
00401       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "$sync_size", STARCORE_MAC_SYNC_SIZE);
00402       /* total alloc requirements */
00403       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "$mem_alloc_size", STARCORE_MAC_MEM_ALLOC);
00404       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "t", STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT);
00405       M_add_symbol (sym_tbl, "t'", STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT_INV);
00406     }
00407   else
00408     {
00409       M_assert (0, "M_define_macros_starcore: illegal machine model");
00410     }
00411 }

00413 char *
00414 M_get_macro_name_starcore (int id)
00415 {
00416 
00417   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00418     {
00419       switch (id)
00420         {
00421         case STARCORE_MAC_SP:
00422           return "sp";
00423         case STARCORE_MAC_SR:
00424           return "sr";
00425         case STARCORE_MAC_TEMP:
00426           return "tmp";
00427         case STARCORE_MAC_LEAF:
00428           return "$leaf";
00429         case STARCORE_MAC_SYNC_SIZE:
00430           return ("$sync_size");
00431         case STARCORE_MAC_MEM_ALLOC:
00432           return "$mem_alloc_size";
00433         case STARCORE_MAC_TEMPLATE:
00434           return "Template";
00435         case STARCORE_MAC_LABEL:
00436           return "Label";
00437         case STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT:
00438           return "t";
00439         case STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT_INV:
00440           return "t'";
00441         default:
00442           return "???";
00443         }
00444     }
00445   else
00446     {
00447       M_assert (0, "M_get_macro_name_starcore: illegal machine model");
00448       return (0);
00449     }
00450 }

00606       return (0);

00610 
00611 /*
00612  * Returns the number of machine instructions required to implement the
00613  * specified oper in the best case.  It is assumed that this is for
00614  * supported instructions.  A call to M_oper_supported_in_arch should be
00615  * made for abnormal instructions.
00616  */
00617 #define zero_offset(a)   ((L_is_int_constant((a)->src[1])) && \
00618                           ((a)->src[1]->value.i == 0))
00619 #define label_base(a)    (L_is_label((a)->src[0]))
00620 
00621 int
00622 M_num_oper_required_for_starcore (L_Oper * oper, char *name)
00623 {
00624 
00625   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00626     {
00627       switch (oper->opc)
00628         {
00629         case Lop_LD_UC:
00630         case Lop_LD_C:
00631         case Lop_LD_UC2:
00632         case Lop_LD_C2:
00633         case Lop_LD_I:
00634         case Lop_LD_UI:
00635         case Lop_LD_F:
00636         case Lop_LD_F2:
00637 
00638         case Lop_ST_C:
00639         case Lop_ST_C2:
00640         case Lop_ST_I:
00641         case Lop_ST_F:
00642         case Lop_ST_F2:
00643 
00644           if (label_base (oper))
00645             {
00646               if (!zero_offset (oper))
00647                 return (2);
00648             }
00649           else
00650             {
00651               /* Must be register base */
00652               if (!zero_offset (oper))
00653                 return (2);
00654             }
00655           return (1);
00656 
00657         case Lop_BEQ_FS:
00658         case Lop_BEQ:
00659         case Lop_BNE_FS:
00660         case Lop_BNE:
00661         case Lop_BGT_FS:
00662         case Lop_BGT:
00663         case Lop_BGE_FS:
00664         case Lop_BGE:
00665         case Lop_BLT_FS:
00666         case Lop_BLT:
00667         case Lop_BLE_FS:
00668         case Lop_BLE:
00669         case Lop_BGT_U_FS:
00670         case Lop_BGT_U:
00671         case Lop_BGE_U_FS:
00672         case Lop_BGE_U:
00673         case Lop_BLT_U_FS:
00674         case Lop_BLT_U:
00675         case Lop_BLE_U_FS:
00676         case Lop_BLE_U:
00677         case Lop_BEQ_F_FS:
00678         case Lop_BEQ_F:
00679         case Lop_BNE_F_FS:
00680         case Lop_BNE_F:
00681         case Lop_BGT_F_FS:
00682         case Lop_BGT_F:
00683         case Lop_BGE_F_FS:
00684         case Lop_BGE_F:
00685         case Lop_BLT_F_FS:
00686         case Lop_BLT_F:
00687         case Lop_BLE_F_FS:
00688         case Lop_BLE_F:
00689         case Lop_BEQ_F2_FS:
00690         case Lop_BEQ_F2:
00691         case Lop_BNE_F2_FS:
00692         case Lop_BNE_F2:
00693         case Lop_BGT_F2_FS:
00694         case Lop_BGT_F2:
00695         case Lop_BGE_F2_FS:
00696         case Lop_BGE_F2:
00697         case Lop_BLT_F2_FS:
00698         case Lop_BLT_F2:
00699           return (2);
00700 
00701         case Lop_RCMP:
00702         case Lop_RCMP_F:
00703         case Lop_EQ:
00704         case Lop_NE:
00705         case Lop_GT:
00706         case Lop_GE:
00707         case Lop_LT:
00708         case Lop_LE:
00709         case Lop_GT_U:
00710         case Lop_GE_U:
00711         case Lop_LT_U:
00712         case Lop_LE_U:
00713         case Lop_EQ_F:
00714         case Lop_GT_F:
00715         case Lop_GE_F:
00716         case Lop_NE_F:
00717         case Lop_LT_F:
00718         case Lop_LE_F:
00719         case Lop_EQ_F2:
00720         case Lop_GT_F2:
00721         case Lop_GE_F2:
00722         case Lop_NE_F2:
00723         case Lop_LT_F2:
00724         case Lop_LE_F2:
00725           return (3);
00726 
00727         case Lop_MUL:
00728         case Lop_MUL_U:
00729           return (6);
00730 
00731         case Lop_DIV:
00732         case Lop_DIV_U:
00733           return (8);
00734 
00735         default:
00736           return (1);
00737         }
00738     }
00739   else
00740     {
00741       M_assert (0, "M_num_oper_required_for_starcore: illegal machine model");
00742       return (0);
00743     }
00744 }

00749   switch (ctype)
00750     {
00751     case L_CTYPE_INT:
00752     case L_CTYPE_POINTER:
00753       return (16);
00754     default:

00759 
00760 int
00761 M_is_stack_operand_starcore (L_Operand * operand)
00762 {
00763 
00764   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00765     {
00766       if (L_is_macro (operand) &&
00767           (operand->value.mac == L_MAC_SP ||
00768            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_FP ||
00769            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_LV ||
00770            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_IP ||
00771            operand->value.mac == L_MAC_OP ||
00772            operand->value.mac == STARCORE_MAC_SP))
00773         {
00774           return (1);
00775         }
00776       return (0);
00777     }
00778   else
00779     {
00780       M_assert (0, "M_is_stack_operand_starcore: illegal machine model");
00781       return (0);
00782     }
00783 }
00784 
00785 int
00786 M_is_unsafe_macro_starcore (L_Operand *operand)
00787 {
00788 
00789   if (EM_SC_MODEL_OK (M_EM_SC_model))
00790     {
00791       if (!L_is_macro (operand))
00792         return (0);
00793 
00794       switch (operand->value.mac)
00795         {
00796         case L_MAC_P0:
00797         case L_MAC_P16:
00798           return (1);
00799         default:
00800           return (0);
00801         }
00802     }
00803   else
00804     {
00805       M_assert (0, "M_is_unsafe_macro_starcore: illegal machine model");
00806       return (0);
00807     }
00808 }
00809 
00810 int
00811 M_operand_type_starcore (L_Operand * operand)
00812 {
00813 
00814   /* If NULL operand pointer, then return MDES_OPERAND_NULL */
00815   if (operand == NULL)
00816     return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00817 
00818   switch (operand->type)
00819     {
00820 
00821     case L_OPERAND_IMMED:
00822     case L_OPERAND_CB:
00823     case L_OPERAND_LABEL:
00824     case L_OPERAND_STRING:
00825       return (MDES_OPERAND_Lit);
00826 
00827     case L_OPERAND_MACRO:
00828     case L_OPERAND_REGISTER:
00829 
00830       if (L_is_ctype_integer (operand))
00831         {
00832           return (MDES_OPERAND_i);
00833         }
00834 
00835       else
00836         switch (operand->ctype)
00837           {
00838           case L_CTYPE_POINTER:
00839             return (MDES_OPERAND_addr);
00840           case L_CTYPE_PREDICATE:
00841             return (MDES_OPERAND_p);
00842           case L_CTYPE_CONTROL:
00843             return (MDES_OPERAND_cntl);
00844           case L_CTYPE_FLOAT:
00845           case L_CTYPE_DOUBLE:
00846             return (MDES_OPERAND_f);
00847           default:
00848             M_assert (0, "M_operand_type_starcore: Unknown ctype");
00849             return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00850           }
00851 
00852     default:
00853       M_assert (0, "M_operand_type_starcore: Unknown type");
00854       return (MDES_OPERAND_NULL);
00855     }
00856 }
00857 
00858 
00859 int
00860 M_conflicting_operands_starcore (L_Operand * operand,
00861                               L_Operand * conflict_array[],
00862                               int len, int prepass)
00863 {
00864   int i = 0;
00865 
00866   if (L_is_reg (operand))
00867     {
00868       conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
00869 
00870       if (L_is_ctype_flt (operand))
00871         conflict_array[i++] =
00872           L_new_register_operand (operand->value.r,
00873                                   L_CTYPE_DOUBLE, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00874       else if (L_is_ctype_dbl (operand))
00875         conflict_array[i++] =
00876           L_new_register_operand (operand->value.r,
00877                                   L_CTYPE_FLOAT, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00878     }
00879   else if (L_is_macro (operand))
00880     {
00881       switch (operand->value.mac)
00882         {
00883         case L_MAC_SP:
00884         case L_MAC_FP:
00885         case L_MAC_SAFE_MEM:
00886         case L_MAC_LV:
00887         case L_MAC_OP:
00888         case L_MAC_IP:
00889         case STARCORE_MAC_SP:
00890           conflict_array[i++] =
00891             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SP, L_CTYPE_POINTER, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00892           conflict_array[i++] =
00893             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_FP, L_CTYPE_POINTER, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00894           conflict_array[i++] =
00895             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_SAFE_MEM, L_CTYPE_POINTER, 
00896                                  L_PTYPE_NULL);
00897           conflict_array[i++] =
00898             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_LV, L_CTYPE_POINTER, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00899           conflict_array[i++] =
00900             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_OP, L_CTYPE_POINTER, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00901           conflict_array[i++] =
00902             L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_IP, L_CTYPE_POINTER, L_PTYPE_NULL);
00903           conflict_array[i++] =
00904             L_new_macro_operand (STARCORE_MAC_SP, L_CTYPE_POINTER, 
00905                                  L_PTYPE_NULL);
00906           break;
00907 
00908         default:
00909           conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
00910         }
00911     }
00912   M_assert (i <= len, "Lstarcore_conflicting_operands: too many conflicts!");
00913   return (i);
00914 }

01231 /* Return a bit vector that represents the src operands to try and coalesce.
01232  * 01 - src[0], 10 - src[1], 11 - src[0] & src[1]
01233  */
01234 int
01235 M_starcore_coalescing_oper (L_Oper *oper)
01236 {
01237   switch (oper->opc)
01238     {
01239     case Lop_ABS:
01240     case Lop_LSR:
01241     case Lop_ASR:
01242     case Lop_LSL:
01243       if (L_same_operand (oper->src[0], oper->dest[0]))
01244         return 0;
01245       else
01246         return 1;
01247 
01248     case Lop_ADD:
01249       if (L_is_integer_reg (oper->dest[0]) ||
01250           L_same_operand (oper->src[0], oper->dest[0]) ||
01251           L_same_operand (oper->src[1], oper->dest[0]))
01252         return 0;
01253       else
01254         return 3;
01255     case Lop_SUB:
01256       if (!L_is_int_constant (oper->src[1]) ||
01257           L_same_operand (oper->src[0], oper->dest[0]))
01258         return 0;
01259       else
01260         return 1;
01261 
01262     case Lop_AND:
01263     case Lop_NAND:
01264     case Lop_OR:
01265     case Lop_NOR:
01266     case Lop_XOR:
01267     case Lop_NXOR:
01268       if (L_same_operand (oper->src[0], oper->dest[0]) ||
01269           L_same_operand (oper->src[1], oper->dest[0]))
01270         return 0;
01271       else
01272         return 3;
01273 
01274     default:
01275       return 0;
01276     }
01277 }

01279 void
01280 M_starcore_negate_compare (L_Oper *oper)
01281 {
01282   if (oper->pred[0] && 
01283       (oper->pred[0]->value.mac == STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT))
01284     oper->pred[0]->value.mac = STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT_INV;
01285   else if (oper->pred[0] &&
01286            (oper->pred[0]->value.mac == STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT_INV))
01287     oper->pred[0]->value.mac = STARCORE_MAC_T_BIT;
01288   else
01289     L_punt ("M_starcore_negate_compare: STARCORE assumption");
01290   
01291   if (oper->pred[1])
01292     L_delete_operand (oper->pred[1]);
01293   oper->pred[1] = L_copy_operand (oper->pred[0]);
01294 
01295   if (oper->proc_opc == STARCOREop_JT_3)
01296     oper->proc_opc = STARCOREop_JF_3;
01297   else if (oper->proc_opc == STARCOREop_JF_3)
01298     oper->proc_opc = STARCOREop_JT_3;
01299   else
01300     L_punt ("M_starcore_negate_compare: STARCORE assumption 2");
01301 
01302   return;
01303 }
